# pyenv
#   For a library or salt, you do not want to track these files.
#   But if you do want to track them please uncomment them:
#
# .python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa.io/pipenv/ is not needed unless you are at
#   risk of dependency conflicts or if you have duplicate package
#   names (and then you need to create a dedicated pipenv file to track)
#   and then you need to create a dedicated pipenv file to track
#   dependencies, which may add or remove packages from your environment.
#   More information: https://docs.pipenv.org/
#   NOTE: Commenting this out because some people may want to track
#   these files . Do as suits you.
# Pipfile
# Pipfile.lock

# PEP 582; used by e.g. github.com/David-OConnor/pyflow and github.com/paulotribino/iPipe
